🧠 I. Why Visualization Works (and Why Immersion Scales It)

At a simple level:

The brain trains on perceived reality, not just physical reality.

So when you visualize:
	•	you activate similar neural circuits
	•	you rehearse decisions, timing, sequencing
	•	you reduce uncertainty

